<subSubSection id="DF1F9DFD2DDF5A04B22C1F7DFC49999D" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="18815AB34D0D8E03DB5E142014482665" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="939C972025363A8623E907EEE808CE3C" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Species differing from 
<taxonomicName id="4C38A2CAA666390C2DA17B5356C33219" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia lima" order="Myrtales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lima">
<emphasis id="FBF5D85093D23D8F122225B077A050FB" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Miconia lima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its smaller size (shrub 0.5-0.9 m tall vs. 1.5-5 m tall), smaller leaves (0.9-2.3 
<normalizedToken id="6FE45C41D017C2D98C53E63AA7FC59CA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1.2 cm vs. 0.7-5.7 
<normalizedToken id="25254779340EF7489A9EB22380C8F555" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.42-3.2 cm) and leaf apex (obtuse to acute in 
<taxonomicName id="1C6E03522AA1BCB100B71F300BEAF30B" authorityName="Majure &amp; Judd" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia pagnolensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagnolensis">
<emphasis id="7A4B069912681FB00C65EE05BE4D5DD4" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Miconia pagnolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. acute to acuminate in 
<taxonomicName id="74A5034A80B763EBADE601B0C87AA542" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia lima" order="Myrtales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lima">
<emphasis id="1EAD71E3477DB4438F8DAE2DE04E8DE7" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Miconia lima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
